    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 2000, 4000, AND 8000 - Before 12/06/1994 - COMPONENTS - HEATER CORE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="2">
        <title>HEATER CORE</title>
        <para>The heater core, constructed of ribbon fins (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1601404">Figures 4</hotlnk>
            and
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1601405">5</hotlnk>), is mounted in the unit housing. Engine coolant is circulated through
            the core, and heat from the coolant is dissipated by air circulated through the core fins.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1601404" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic id="g1601404" filename="../figg16/G1601404.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="368px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 4. Blend-Air Unit Heater Core (Exploded View)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. INNER SEAL</callout1>
                <callout1>2. HEATER CORE</callout1>
                <callout1>3. OUTER SEAL</callout1>
                <callout1>4. CLAMP</callout1>
                <callout1>5. COOLANT (WATER) HOSE</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1601405" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic id="g1601405" filename="../figg16/G1601405.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                     scalefitheight="432px"/>
            <caption>Figure 5. Heater (Only) Unit Heater Core (Exploded View)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. HEATER UNIT</callout1>
                <callout1>2. SEAL</callout1>
                <callout1>3. SCREW</callout1>
                <callout1>4. HEATER CORE</callout1>
                <callout1>5. SEAL</callout1>
                <callout1>6. BLEND AIR DOOR ASSEMBLY</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
